imdb.plot outline: Austin's sonic journey is a fascinating ride that started from classic blues/psychedelic rock to a global sound palette encompassing jazz, R&B, Avant-Garde, Electronic, World and Musical Theater. You can go to Threadgill's and see paintings of Janis Joplin lining the walls. You can walk down 6th street and see 5-foot ceramic guitar statues on the sidewalks. Now that Austin is known for events such as ACL and South By Southwest, the question remains - what is the Austin sound? This mini-documentary series aims to answer that question - and also to discover what sound Austin is known for. We will be doing short interviews with several different artists that have won the Austin Music Awards.
imdb.title: What is the Austin Sound?
